SUMMARY:Longford Park and Reynold's Dog Park- route along canal
DESCRIPTION:Walking Tails\nThis week we will walk along the canal. The tra
 il in this direction is dirt and gravel. We will go out about 1.5 miles an
 d then come back the way we came\, for a total of 3 miles. CLICK DIRECTLY 
 ON THE MAP IF YOU THINK YOU ARE LOST. IT WILL BRING YOU RIGHT TO US WHERE 
 WE MEET.\n\nWe will be meeting near the dog park\, come early and let your
  dog play off leash in the dog park.\n\nStart Time: We will start hiking p
 romptly at the scheduled time.\n\nDuration of the walk – depends on the 
 people and dogs in the group. We frequently end up walking in smaller pack
 s based on the comfort level of the participants. In the past this walk ta
 kes about 1 hour or so.\n\nPlease remember pooh bags and that your dog mus
 t be on a leash that is no more than 10 feet long.\n\nFacilities: There ar
 e bathrooms at the dog park\n\nNOTICE: By attending this event you are agr
 eeing that YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR YOUR OWN SAFETY AT ALL TIMES. The hike 
 leader and other members cannot be held responsible for any damages\, acci
 dents\, or liabilities incurred while hiking with us.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/walking-tails/events/313698108/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260308T184256Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260308T184256Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visitlancastercity": "https://visitlancastercity.com/event/spring-equinox-yoga/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visitlancastercity
X-SOURCE:Visitlancastercity
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260315T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260315T110000
DTSTAMP:20260312T132647
CREATED:20260304T163821Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T163822Z
UID:56710-1773568800-1773572400@visitlancastercity.com
SUMMARY:Spring Equinox Yoga
DESCRIPTION:Welcome spring with a gentle\, beginner-friendly yoga class focused on breath\, movement\, and the calming presence of plants. \n\n\n\nJoin yoga teacher Maggie Mowery for an hour-long yoga class inspired by the Spring Equinox and the sense of balance\, renewal\, and new beginnings it brings. This grounding session invites you to reconnect with yourself as the seasons shift and will include breath awareness\, gentle movement\, and a guided meditation. Maggie is an E-RYT 200 certified yoga teacher with over eight years of teaching experience and specializes in beginner-friendly\, accessible\, alignment-based yoga. This class is well suited for those new to yoga as well as seasoned yogis looking for a mindful\, nurturing practice.When she’s not on the mat\, Maggie loves to paint\, sculpt in clay\, spend time in nature or her garden\, and be with loved ones. She and her partner also regularly volunteer at Lancaster Farm Sanctuary in Mount Joy\, PA. \n\n\n\nAfter the session\, attendees are invited to shop and enjoy an exclusive 20% off before 12pm. \n\n\n\nPlease note that this class will be held upstairs in our Loft area and is accessible by stairs only.
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/spring-equinox-yoga/
LOCATION:Gallery Grow Plant Bar\, 320 N Queen St.\, Lancaster\, Pennsylvania\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes and Workshops
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitlancastercity.com/wp-content/uploads/Spring-Equinox-Yoga2160-x-1080.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Gallery Grow Plant Bar":MAILTO:contact@gallerygrow.com
END:VEVENT
