SUMMARY:Stevens & Smith with the Lancaster Symphony Orchestra!
DESCRIPTION:Join the Lancaster Symphony Orchestra! Celebrate the 250th birthday of the United States and the grand opening of the Thaddeus Stevens & Lydia Hamilton Smith Center for History and Democracy with Aaron Copland’s Lincoln Portrait\, William L. Dawson’s Negro Folk Symphony\, and a powerful new work celebrating the lives of Stevens & Smith by Lancaster’s own D. Michael Wege. Join us 45-minutes before each performance for a free pre-concert lecture. Click the link below for ticket information or call our box office at 717-291-6440 ext 1. Showtime: Friday\, March 13\, 2026 @ 7:30 PM Saturday\, March 14\, 2026 @ 2:30 PM Saturday\, March 14\, 2026 @ 7:30 PM Sunday\, March 15\, 2026 @ 2:30 PM Program: Aaron Copland – A Lincoln Portrait D Michael Wege – Second Founding William L. Dawson – Negro Folk Symphony
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/stevens-smith-with-the-lancaster-symphony-orchestra/
LOCATION:Gardner Theatre within Lancaster Country Day School\, 725 Hamilton Road\, Lancaster\, Pennsylvania\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Music and Dance
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitlancastercity.com/wp-content/uploads/Stevens-Smith.jpg
