LAST-MODIFIED:20260116T152802Z
UID:10073977-1773774000-1773777600@www.saintjameslancaster.org
SUMMARY:Contemplative Tuesday
DESCRIPTION:7 – 8:00 PM in the Chapel\nTuesdays\, February 10 – March 24\nIn person and via Zoom \nThis seven-week series explores the question: What kind of person must I become to live non-violently? \nTogether\, we will reflect on what we mean by non-violence—and what we mean by violence—drawing from scripture\, contemplative practice\, and the wisdom of those throughout history who have wrestled with this question before us. Through guided reflection\, shared conversation and embodied practices\, we will explore how inner formation shapes outer action\, and how a grounded\, compassionate presence becomes the foundation for loving resistance in the world. \nClick here to register.
URL:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/event/contemplative-tuesday/2026-03-17/
LOCATION:Saint James Chapel\, 103 North Duke Street\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17602\, United States
CATEGORIES:Contemplative Citizenship,Contemplative Meditation,Contemplative Practice,Contemplative Prayer
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.saintjameslancaster.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/FEATURED-IMAGE-Contemplative-Tuesdays-copy-2.jpg
GEO:40.040058;-76.30344
