LAST-MODIFIED:20251110T172022Z
UID:10000352-1774461600-1774468800@zestchef.com
SUMMARY:2739 - Bakes from Spring Market
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the bright\, fruit-forward flavors of the season in this hands-on baking class with Chef Faith Kennedy. Learn how to create tender\, oil-based cakes that highlight the beauty of fresh produce – from zesty citrus to early rhubarb. Explore techniques for building moisture\, balancing sweetness\, and finishing with natural glazes that make every slice shine. This class is all about bringing the freshness of the farmers market into your spring kitchen. \nHands on. BYOB. Ages 16 and up \n\nOlive Oil Citrus Loaf with Thyme Glaze\nRhubarb Upside-Down Cake with Caramelized Edges
URL:https://zestchef.com/class/2739-bakes-from-spring-market/
LOCATION:Zest Cooking School\, 1180 Erbs Quarry Road\, Lititz\, PA\, 17543\, United States
CATEGORIES:Basics and Techniques,Dessert,Let's Bake,Seasonal,Vegetarian
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://zestchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/market--e1762387626220.jpg
END:VEVENT
