BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Amtshows": "https://amtshows.com/show/dr-seuss-the-cat-in-the-hat-live-on-stage/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:amtshows
X-SOURCE:Amtshows
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260326T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260326T180000
DTSTAMP:20260313T235930
CREATED:20250728T133016Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251119T193601Z
UID:10001800-1774548000-1774548000@amtshows.com
SUMMARY:Dr. Seuss The Cat in the Hat - Live on Stage!
DESCRIPTION:Tickets: $29 $39 $49 $59 \nThe kids are bored.. again..! What to do with YOUR Thing One and Thing 2?! \nHere’s an idea: Bring the whole family to the Worlds Number 1 ‘The Cat in the Hat’ show for an experience they’ll never forget. The story has been around for over 50 years and kids still love it… just like you did! \nTwo bored kids (This was way before iPads). One rainy day (We’ve all had a few of those) And one crazy cat wearing a red-striped hat (Where was the background check for that babysitter?!) \nIn 1957\, Dr Seuss used only 200 words to write his classic tale. More than 50 years later\, The Cat in the Hat is a much-loved children’s phenomenon. The play was adapted for the stage in 2009 by the National Theatre of Britain. The Cat in The Hat interrupts this rainy afternoon with his unexpected visit to Sally and her brother’s cozy home. Their outspoken and outraged pet Fish is astounded and concerned\, but this cat will not be deterred. He will teach us all to make our own fun with nothing but a little imagination. “It’s fun to have fun\, but you have to know how” Along with Thing One and Thing Two\, the cat will fill the theatre with mischievous humour and madcap style. \nA timeless tale with a twist—this energetic adaptation bursts onto the stage (and maybe into the aisles). Expect laughs\, surprises\, and just a bit of delightful disorder! \nFor certain concerts\, audience members may prefer to stand or dance\, especially when encouraged by the artist to do so. Guest expectations differ\, so we simply ask all attendees to extend mutual respect toward one another and maintain awareness of those around them. Our staff will only intervene in matters of safety or when behavior is deemed unruly\, combative\, or disruptive to the overall performance.
URL:https://amtshows.com/show/dr-seuss-the-cat-in-the-hat-live-on-stage/
LOCATION:American Music Theatre\, 2425 Lincoln Hwy East\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17605\, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebrity Concerts,Children's Shows
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://amtshows.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/CITH_Concessions-Events-and-News-for-Website-1920x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Apostlesucc": "https://apostlesucc.org/event/asking-the-hard-questions-6/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:apostlesucc
X-SOURCE:Apostlesucc
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260326T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260326T190000
DTSTAMP:20260313T235928
CREATED:20260106T183110Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260106T183110Z
UID:37762-1774548000-1774551600@apostlesucc.org
SUMMARY:Asking the Hard Questions
DESCRIPTION:At Church of the Apostles\, we know many are carrying deep and honest questions about faith\, especially in light of what is happening in our country and throughout the world. Questions like “Where is God in all of this?” are not signs of weak faith\, but part of a faithful journey we are called to walk together. \nTo create space for these conversations\, we invite you to a new monthly series\, Asking the Hard Questions\, hosted by our seminary intern\, Deklan Lewis\, in the Parlor. Together\, we will explore doubt\, struggle\, and belief as meaningful parts of discipleship. Our first two gatherings will include viewing and discussing the film God on Trial as we wrestle\, much like Jacob\, with faith and what it means to follow Jesus today. \nTo accommodate different schedules\, two sessions will be offered each month: Monday morning\, March 23rd at 10 AM\, and Thursday evening\, March 26th at 6 PM. All are welcome to join this thoughtful\, open\, and supportive conversation.
URL:https://apostlesucc.org/event/asking-the-hard-questions-6/
LOCATION:Church of the Apostles UCC\, 1850 Marietta Ave\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://apostlesucc.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Asking-the-Hard-Questions-with-Deklan-Lewis.jpg
END:VEVENT
