BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Amtshows": "https://amtshows.com/show/my-generation-tour-the-lovin-spoonful-terry-sylvester-and-gary-lewis-the-playboys/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:amtshows
X-SOURCE:Amtshows
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T190000
DTSTAMP:20260313T235930
CREATED:20250929T133011Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250925T200439Z
UID:10001819-1777230000-1777230000@amtshows.com
SUMMARY:My Generation Tour: The Lovin Spoonful\, Terry Sylvester and Gary Lewis & The Playboys
DESCRIPTION:Tickets: $49 $59 $79 $89\nAMT Member Pre-Sale: Wednesday\, October 1 at 10:00 a.m.\nPublic On-Sale: Friday\, October 3 at 10:00 a.m. \n“This good-time spectacular celebrates the time of our lives with all three acts performing with their own full bands spanning the golden singles-era of pop music\, from 1965 to 1975. This was the magic time where hit singles ruled the charts and won our hearts\,” producer Jim Della Croce exclaims. Terry Sylvester\, who famously replaced Graham Nash after he left The Hollies\, will perform along with famed pop legend Gary Lewis. “This show is the baby-boomer bucket list must see event of the year\, a hip trip back to the era that defined our generation\,” he concludes. \nBetween The Lovin’ Spoonful\, The Hollies\, and Gary Lewis and The Playboys\, the charts exploded every week with a new tune that captivated our rock and roll souls. Nearly 30 hits will explode throughout this two-hour celebration: “Daydream\,” “Do You Believe in Magic\,” “This Diamond Ring\,” “Carrie Anne\,” “Long Cool Woman (in a Black Dress)\, “Count Me In\,” “He Ain’t Heavy\, He’s My Brother\,” “Summer in the City\,” “She’s Just My Style\,” “You Didn’t Have to Be So Nice\,” “On a Carousel\,”  “Sure Gonna Miss Her” and “The Air that I Breathe.” \nFor certain concerts\, audience members may prefer to stand or dance\, especially when encouraged by the artist to do so. Guest expectations differ\, so we simply ask all attendees to extend mutual respect toward one another and maintain awareness of those around them. Our staff will only intervene in matters of safety or when behavior is deemed unruly\, combative\, or disruptive to the overall performance.
URL:https://amtshows.com/show/my-generation-tour-the-lovin-spoonful-terry-sylvester-and-gary-lewis-the-playboys/
LOCATION:American Music Theatre\, 2425 Lincoln Hwy East\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17605\, United States
CATEGORIES:Celebrity Concerts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://amtshows.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MGT_Concessions-Events-and-News-for-Website-1920x1080-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Apostlesucc": "https://apostlesucc.org/event/asking-the-hard-questions-7/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:apostlesucc
X-SOURCE:Apostlesucc
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260427T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260427T110000
DTSTAMP:20260313T235928
CREATED:20260106T184313Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260106T184313Z
UID:37781-1777284000-1777287600@apostlesucc.org
SUMMARY:Asking the Hard Questions
DESCRIPTION:At Church of the Apostles\, we know many are carrying deep and honest questions about faith\, especially in light of what is happening in our country and throughout the world. Questions like “Where is God in all of this?” are not signs of weak faith\, but part of a faithful journey we are called to walk together. \nTo create space for these conversations\, we invite you to a new monthly series\, Asking the Hard Questions\, hosted by our seminary intern\, Deklan Lewis\, in the Parlor. Together\, we will explore doubt\, struggle\, and belief as meaningful parts of discipleship. Our first two gatherings will include viewing and discussing the film God on Trial as we wrestle\, much like Jacob\, with faith and what it means to follow Jesus today. \nTo accommodate different schedules\, two sessions will be offered each month: Monday morning\, April 27th at 10 AM\, and Thursday evening\, April 30th at 6 PM. All are welcome to join this thoughtful\, open\, and supportive conversation.
URL:https://apostlesucc.org/event/asking-the-hard-questions-7/
LOCATION:Church of the Apostles UCC\, 1850 Marietta Ave\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17603\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://apostlesucc.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Asking-the-Hard-Questions-with-Deklan-Lewis.jpg
END:VEVENT
