BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancasterbirdclub": "https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/chickies-rock-warbler-walk/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancasterbirdclub
X-SOURCE:Lancasterbirdclub
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T070000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T110000
DTSTAMP:20260313T235933
CREATED:20240407T073418Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260128T214206Z
UID:1522-1777705200-1777719600@lancasterbirdclub.org
SUMMARY:Chickies Rock Warbler Walk
DESCRIPTION:Marie Johnston will lead a field trip to Chickies Rock County Park. Meet at 7 a.m. at Breezy View Overlook along Rt. 441 just north of Columbia. After birding Breezy View\, which includes a view of a Bald Eagle’s nest on the York County side of the Susquehanna River\, the group will proceed to the Chickies Rock Overlook parking lot and bird in the park on both sides of Rt. 441. The field trip will end in the day-use area of the park. In addition to warblers\, target species include orioles\, tanagers\, and flycatchers. Be prepared for ticks and bring water and snacks/lunch. Contact Marie (717-413-2086 or mariejohnston303@gmail.com) if you have questions or by 6 p.m. on the previous day if you plan to attend. \nMeeting Location: Breezy View Overlook near 770 Breezyview Dr.\, Columbia\, PA 17512\nContact: Marie Johnston\, 717-413-2086\, mariejohnston303@gmail.com
URL:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/chickies-rock-warbler-walk/
LOCATION:Chickies Rock Breezy View Overlook (Meeting Location)\, 770 Breezyview Dr.\, Columbia\, PA\, 17512\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/47954985173_423dd0452c_o.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lancasterbirdclub": "https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/pumping-station-road-warbler-walk/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lancasterbirdclub
X-SOURCE:Lancasterbirdclub
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T120000
DTSTAMP:20260313T235933
CREATED:20240407T074148Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260128T161753Z
UID:1530-1777708800-1777723200@lancasterbirdclub.org
SUMMARY:Pumping Station Road Warbler Walk
DESCRIPTION:Carl Groff will lead the Pumping Station Rd. Warbler Walk. Meet at 8 a.m. at the parking lot at Rt. 322 and Pumping Station Road. The morning will be spent looking for migrants and resident birds along this popular stretch of Hammer Creek. A wide variety of birds are possible with special attention paid to the warblers that use this area as their home or a brief stopover during migration. Some other target birds will include thrushes\, flycatchers\, tanagers\, orioles and grosbeaks. This trip will last until around noontime so dress for the weather. Please contact Carl at 717-471-9969 or fledge19@verizon.net by 6 p.m. the previous day if you plan to attend. \nMeeting Location: Horseshoe Trail Parking Lot near 80 Pumping Station Rd.\, Lititz\, PA 17543\nContact: Carl Groff\, 717-471-9969 or fledge19@verizon.net 
URL:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/pumping-station-road-warbler-walk/
LOCATION:Horseshoe Trail Parking Lot at U.S. Route 322 & Pumping Station Road\, 80 Pumping Station Rd.\, Lititz\, PA\, 17543\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/53728006265_3b879efdb2_o.jpeg
END:VEVENT
